@jbp7047 sorry about the late reply, I just saw this. Seems like you're running index.mjs, so it's defaulting to ESM modules (or via `"type": "module"` on your package.json). How are you compiling your project?

I found an opened thread about this on AWS repo's, could it be related? https://github.com/aws/aws-sam-cli/issues/4827

Feel free to open an issue if your problem persists: https://github.com/qdrant/qdrant-js/issues

@tomasz_library_one Hi! Seems like we released a dependency which has a dependency which is lacking CJS support, and only exports an ESM module. While we fix this, you could override that dependency in your `package.json` and PIN it to its previous version, which was working. If you're using yarn or pnpm there are ways, with NPM it's done via `overrides` (https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/configuring-npm/package-json#overrides), e.g.:

```json
"overrides": {
  "@qdrant/openapi-typescript-fetch": "1.2.1"
}
```

